-- Foxconn Technology to Build Research Center in Shanghai
-- B y   T i m   C u l p a n
-- 2012-05-08T09:27:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/foxconn-technology-to-build-research-center-in-shanghai.html
Foxconn Technology Group, the world’s
largest contract manufacturer of electronics, plans to build a
research and development center in  Shanghai ’s Pudong District,
the Taipei-based company said in an invitation to a
groundbreaking ceremony for the site.  China sales, electronic-commerce and research teams will be
housed in the new complex, which is expected to be completed in
early 2015, Foxconn said. Chairman and Founder Terry Gou plans
to preside over the event on May 10, Simon Hsing, spokesman for
Foxconn’s Taipei-listed flagship  Hon Hai Precision Industry Co. (2317) ,
said by phone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Culpan in Taipei at 
